The article is a proclamation by President Donald J. Trump, issued on November 8, 2017, in commemoration of World Freedom Day. The proclamation reflects on the fall of the Berlin Wall on November 9, 1989, and celebrates the triumph of freedom over Communism. It acknowledges the courage of those who fought for a better future and emphasizes the importance of democratic values and human rights. The proclamation also recognizes the ongoing threats of terrorism and extremism and highlights the need for nations to work together to secure and advance freedom and stability. President Trump calls upon the people of the United States to observe World Freedom Day with appropriate ceremonies and activities, reaffirming their dedication to freedom and democracy.